Recommendation:

undertake immediate remedial measure to make the structure operational, otherwise this may cause audit disallowance for the total cost of the project;
direct the contractor’s workers to vacate the slaughter house and establish their own campsite for workers.

Recommendation:

Instruct the Municipal Health Officer to:

maintain proper recording and safe storage of medical and dental supplies which will be controlled by designated competent personnel; 
report all received supplies and equipment from DOH and other agencies to the Municipal Mayor copy furnished the Municipal Accountant for recording in the books; 
prepare and submit utilization/issuance of medical and dental supplies to the Municipal Accountant to recognize expense account every end of the month; and
maintain monitoring template to properly handle the inventory accounts as to receipts, utilizations and balances.

Recommendation:

exercise prudence and diligence in the disbursement of the 20 percent Development Fund and; 
to strictly adhere to DILG-DBM Joint Memorandum Circular (JMC) No. 2017-1 in the utilization of the 20 percent Development Fund, otherwise this may result to audit disallowance.

Recommendation:

re-evaluate the system, document all problem encountered and communicate in writing to the ECPAC provider for the immediate enhancement of the system;
determine if there is a need to continue the subscription of the Accounting System considering the deficiencies noted and the prompt response of the ECPAC Provider to address the same. If so, execute a contract that fully defined the desired services and outputs of the said system, such as but limited to:
consistency of data in the ledgers, statements and other templates/outputs;
provision of user’s manual, system’s flow diagram and other related ECPAC Accounting System tools;
availability of facilities which are already featured in the system as raised in item c above or in Annex M and the facility for data extraction;
frequency of visitation for monitoring the efficiency and continuity of the system’s operations; and
reasonable contract period considering that the government will be providing a uniform accounting system in the near future.

direct the Treasurer, Accountant, Budget Officer and other concerned officials to: (i) prioritize the conduct in-depth analysis of the accumulated cash balances to identify trust liabilities and funds free from obligations; (ii) study and discuss among themselves opportunity to earn additional income thru prudent investment of idle funds; and (iii) if feasible, prepare a proposal for investment;
coordinate to the officials of authorized depository banks for further understanding of investment programs offered that helps in effective decision making; and 
submit the proposal to the Sangguniang Bayan for its review and approval.

direct the Municipal Inventory Committee to (i) perform a physical count of inventories in order to establish the actual inventory on-hand for all offices under the Municipal Government of Tagana-an; (ii) consolidate all inventory on-hand; and (iii) coordinate with the Municipal Accountant in the reconciliation of inventory accounts to arrive at the accurate and actual amounts; 
instruct the Municipal Accountant to (i) comply PPSAS 12, that is, record the purchases of supplies and materials as inventory and recognize expense when the inventories are consumed or distributed; (ii) coordinate with the Municipal Inventory Committee in the reconciliation of inventory accounts; and (iii) prepare JEV to adjust the reconciling items; and 
designate competent personnel to handle the general services particularly to (i) perform the custodianship of supplies and materials; and (ii) prepare RSMI and submit to the Accountant for the recognition of expense account in the consumption or distribution of inventories.

direct all the concerned officials/employees to (i) immediately settle the outstanding cash advances; and (ii) all advances must be liquidated at year-end and thereafter;
instruct the Accountant to (i) deduct from the salaries of the concerned officials/personnel the long outstanding advances if they fail to settle at due time; (ii) refrain from granting additional cash advances unless otherwise the previous advance is liquidated; and (iii) coordinate with national agencies top management to direct those officials/employees previously assigned in the municipality to immediately settle their outstanding accounts; and
file a request for authority to write-off the receivables to COA Regional Director with complete supporting documents, if after exhausting all means failed to locate the inactive personnel and family of deceased accountable officers; (c) adhere to the regulations in the granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances.

Instruct the Municipal Health Officer to:

maintain proper recording and safe storage of medical and dental supplies which will be controlled by designated competent personnel; 
report all received supplies and equipment from DOH and other agencies to the Municipal Mayor copy furnished the Municipal Accountant for recording in the books; 
prepare and submit utilization/issuance of medical and dental supplies to the Municipal Accountant to recognize expense account every end of the month; and
maintain monitoring template to properly handle the inventory accounts as to receipts, utilizations and balances.

advise the concerned officials to conduct the estimation of revenue based on the previous years’ actual revenue realized;
conduct LSB planning and budgeting compliant to DepEd, DBM and DILG Joint Circular No. 1 series of 2017; and
inform LSB on the available accumulated fund for additional projects/activities thru issuance of supplemental appropriation ordinance.

intensify planning of proposed projects to (i) consider the most priority that should be accomplished for the timely use of the projects without sacrificing the quality of work; (ii) conduct effective survey of project locations in order to prepare the appropriate plans and specifications; (iii) consider the available materials in the market; and (iii) ensure the locations are owned by the government;
consider hiring additional technical personnel in Engineering Office to fast tract the unattended workloads; and
enhance monitoring control in the implementation projects including the procurement process to immediately address problems encountered that could affect its timely completion.

re-evaluate the system, document all problem encountered and communicate in writing to the ECPAC provider for the immediate enhancement of the system;
determine if there is a need to continue the subscription of the Accounting System considering the deficiencies noted and the prompt response of the ECPAC Provider to address the same. If so, execute a contract that fully defined the desired services and outputs of the said system, such as but not limited to:
consistency of data in the ledgers, statements and other templates/outputs;
provision of user’s manual, system’s flow diagram and other related ECPAC Accounting System tools;
availability of facilities which are already featured in the system as raised in item c above or in Annex M and the facility for data extraction;
frequency of visitation for monitoring the efficiency and continuity of the system’s operations; and
reasonable contract period considering that the government will be providing a uniform accounting system in the near future.

adhere to the regulations on real property tax as provided in Articles 346 and 362 of the IRR of  RA 7160; 
instruct the Municipal Treasurer to conduct more intense action for the collection of delinquent accounts by prompting the issuance of notices to defaulting taxpayers and warrant of levy before the public auction; and 
advise the Accountant to motivate the barangay officials to assist in collecting the delinquent accounts of property taxes located at their concerned barangays by prompting the release of share of property tax collected duly supported with template on the computation of shares.

submit written justification for not rescinding or terminating the contract despite significant negative slippage was already incurred by the contractor as required in Section 8.4 Annex E and Part III.A.2.b Appendix 4 of the Revised IRR of RA 9184; 
establish immediately a control that will segregate the plan, undertake and review of infrastructure projects; 
strengthen the monitoring control on infrastructure projects by conducting a regular inspection on site and timely submission of reports by a reliable personnel; and 
adhere strictly the provisions under Section 8.4 Annex E and Part III.A.2.b Appendix 4 of the Revised IRR of RA 9184.

Establish an inspectorate team who will undertake review and check the projects other than the persons who are involved directly in the implementation of the projects; 
Stop the practice of allowing the same personnel to initiate, undertake and review the projects/activities, that is, segregate the planning, execution and review/inspection of the project; and 
Hire additional personnel who will handle the planning phase of the infrastructure projects.

Advise the contractor to refund the excess amount claimed;
Adhere strictly the regulations on the prevention and disallowance of excessive expenditures as provided in COA Circular No. 2012-003;
Establish immediately a control that will segregate the plan, undertake and review of infrastructure projects, otherwise recurrence of the same deficiency in the future may result to appropriate legal sanction under RA 3019 or the Anti-Graft and Corrupt Practices Act and the Revised Penal Code towards erring officials/employees; and 
Strengthen the monitoring control on infrastructure projects by conducting a regular inspection on site and timely submission of reports by a reliable personnel.

Coordinate with PPDO - Provincial Government of Surigao and DILG for the schedule of GAD trainings particularly on gender sensitivity, responsive planning and budgeting, analysis and mainstreaming, and submit list of recommended participants;    
Immediately after the trainings, conduct a gender analysis and mainstreaming of programs/activities/projects and prepare a revised GAD Plan and Budget for CY 2015 using the prescribed form as presented in Annex C and at the end of the year prepare the Accomplishment Report using the prescribed form; 
Submit the revised GAD Plan and Budget to PPDO of the Provincial Government to ensure alignment of the municipality GAD PPAs with the priorities of the province, then from PPDO to DILG Regional Office; and 
Furnish the Office of the Auditor with the revised GAD Plan and Budget duly reviewed and certificate of approval from the DILG Regional Office.

Give priority on the implementation of MDRRMF PAPs in order to be prepared in the possible disaster in the future and to avoid possible loss of life and property; 
Identify additional PAPs for the unused/unutilized funds under preparedness and mitigation aspect; and 
Instruct the MDRRM Focal Person to execute his duties and responsibilities as provided in the LDRRMF guidelines.

