Enhance monitoring control in the implementation projects including the procurement process to immediately address problems encountered that could affect its timely completion.

Direct all the concerned officials/employees to (i) coordinate with the end-users of the project during the planning phase in order to fully define their needs; and (ii) fast track the completion of the projects in order to attain the BUB objectives; 

Advise the Accountant to (i) coordinate with the implementing offices for the timely submission of the liquidation reports to the source agency in order to avoid delay in the succeeding releases; and (ii) separate the recording of transactions per project in order to ascertain the actual status of funds and actual physical accomplishment; 

Advise the Municipal Agriculturist to (i) prepare a more comprehensive project proposal with back-up computation and the required process period for agriculture and marine projects to explain the quantity of required materials/supplies, in future similar projects; (ii) consider alternative source for scarce or banned materials like hardwood (iii) coordinate with the Municipal Accountant for the timely preparation and submission of the liquidation reports; 

Instruct the Municipal Government Officials involved in the monitoring of BUB projects to strengthen the monitoring control by conducting a timely evaluation and inspection of projects in order to address immediately the identified problems for its timely completion; 

Advise the Bids and Awards Committee and concerned personnel in-charge of procurement to (i) revisit the procurement processes, identify points of possible delay and establish measures to address the flaw to avoid recurrence of delay in the future similar projects; and (ii) maintain an updated roster of suppliers for agriculture and marine products needed as well as scarce materials for the implementation of projects; and 

In future similar transaction, advice the Municipal Engineer to conduct effective and efficient planning thru project site inspection by technical personnel in coordination with beneficiaries to avoid delay and adjustments in the implementation of project.

Require the contractor to engage the catch-up program in order to fast track the completion of the project to avoid rescindment of contract as stipulated in Section 68 of RA 9184; 

Conduct an inventory of work accomplished by the contractor and impose liquidated damages at least equal to one-tenth of one percent (0.1%) of the cost of the unperformed portion for every day of delay; 

Intensify monitoring of project in order to avoid recurrence of delay to other projects;

Adhere to the regulations on the posting of signboard in the project location as soon as the award has been made in order to inform the public, in the future similar project.

